  <itemBody>
    <div class="grid-row">
      <div class="col-12">
        <h4>Before the premiere, the theater is hosting a rehearsal for some students in 3rd grade. You want to hear what the students think about the piece. Therefore you create a questionaire that the students will recieve afterwards.</h4>
        <h5>Requirenments:<br/>
• The questions have to be relevant for the age group.<br/>
• The questions have to give information that can be used to better the play before the premiere.</h5>
        <h6> Pick two questions from the list that you think should be in the questionaire.</h6>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-row">
      <div class="col-12">
        <choiceInteraction responseIdentifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" maxChoices="2" minChoices="0" orientation="vertical">
          <simpleChoice identifier="choice_1" fixed="false" showHide="show">Have you been to the theater before?</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="choice_2" fixed="false" showHide="show">What could make the play more exciting?</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="choice_4" fixed="false" showHide="show">What is your favorite theater piece?</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="choice_5" fixed="false" showHide="show">Did you like the knight theme, or do you think the play should be about something entirely different?</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="choice_6" fixed="false" showHide="show">What was the most boring part of the play?</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="choice_7" fixed="false" showHide="show">What genre is your favorite?</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="choice_10" fixed="false" showHide="show">Do you think it is too expensive to go to the theater?</simpleChoice>
        </choiceInteraction>
      </div>
    </div>
